<br>
These are some interesting replies. So far in the few pickup and mixed guild/stranger groups I have been in this has not been an issue. the melee's just didn't consider rolling. But, I also see both sides of the coin, and I think a lot of melee do also. After all, that parchment could mean the cash for buying a windblade in the bazaar for a pure melee. <br>
<br>
I never even considered rolling until I read that thread.<br>
And I don't think I ever will. I group with frinds too often and I would just give what ever spells I got to them. Though, I think that on some of the other boards there is some resentment rising among the melee because they aren't seeing any sort of power upgrades for the same time and effort that the casters are getting.<br>
<br>
I think that VI should allow melee to gain similar upgrades through a similar process. Sure, you might not need what ever you got but it could be something to sell or trade for better, just like the parchment spell system. Rather than going through the long quests where you need 20 different drops from 3 different zones, it would be nice to only need one rare drop from any zone.<br>
<br>
Though I like the idea of the parchment system (it prevents one group of people from farming the one much needed spell and driving up the price enormously. I think they need to put class flags on the parchments and that may clear up a lot of the issue... but of course caster class X would complain that class Y gets a better drop rate on parchments.<br>
<br>
In anycase, I think this is a bit of an unbalanced system and VI should take some steps to tweek it.<br>
<br>
 <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
Half Elven Warlord of 61 Battles<br>
