<br>
By the time I am 65 and have most of the AAs I want, I'm going to assume that most of the casters I am with have a lot of their spells as well.  Since no melee loot is dropping, I will be insisting on parchment rolls.  If I start seeing melee stuff drop and the casters are fairly uniformly bowing out of the rolls then I will not roll on any parchments.<br>
<br>
I used to always preach NBG even in pickup groups but have since realised that in most cases the "need" component is missing.  How the hell do I know if caster_01 needs that spell?  By the same token how does he know when uber_1hander_01 drops that I don't already have better since I am using a 2 hander?  How many people do you think would honestly bow out if they didn't need it?  In my experience, very few.<br>
<br>
If I'm in a guild group then it's NBG all the way.  In a pickup it's open lotto on everything, including the stuff I need. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
